[normal] You make a number of assertions about the Ext
[normal]ernal Review of the LGO carried out last year by Richard Thomas CBE, Jim Martin and Dr Kirkham of Sheffield University, specifically that it lacked independence and objectivity and was an “adulatory whitewash”. Furthermore, you make allegations that the pr
[normal]ocess was dominated by Dr Kirkham, whom you describe as a “propagandist” for the LGO. These are serious allegations which from the contents of your submission and from the 2005 article you cite do not appear to be supported by detailed evidence. Before dec
[normal]iding what action to take in respect of your submission, the Committee would be grateful for a further submission setting out in detail your evidence to 
[normal]substantiate these contentions.”
